[TITLE]The Caravan's Departure[/TITLE]
[P]The dwarves begin packing their belongings.  They advise you
that wide roads, and bridges if necessary, are the surest way
to attract the well-stocked wagons of human traders that
travel out from their vast cities above the earth.
Be sure that the road leads right to your depot.  These humans
aren't very hardy; rough terrain taxes them.  Even raw stone floors!  Bah!
